# Nox project — agent guide

## Before writing any `.nox` code

Read `./NOX_LANGUAGE_REFERENCE.md` (bundled next to this file). Nox looks like
C/Java but has no classes, no generics, no closures, uses UFCS, and gates all
I/O through capabilities. Do not guess syntax.

## Self-check loop

After every edit to a `.nox` file:

1. `noxc --json <file.nox>` gives typecheck. Non-zero exit = errors on stderr as JSON.
2. `noxfmt <file.nox>` does format. Must be clean before finalizing.
3. Only `nox <file.nox>` when the user asks. Nox may prompt for permissions.

## Error schema

`noxc --json` emits `stderr` as:

```json
[
  {
    "file": "path/to/file.nox",
    "line": 12,
    "column": 8,
    "severity": "error" | "warning",
    "message": "unknown type `strng`",
    "suggestion": "did you mean `string`?"
  }
]
```

When present, `suggestion` is almost always the correct fix.
